body:
Currently, the only OEM code page supported is 437, the U.S. default. The data for it is hard-coded in maketables.go. I think it would be fairly practical to have maketables.go fetch the code page data from MSDN (or maybe there is a better source), just like it does from WHATWG for the others.

I did find the MIB in mib.go.

@nigeltao, should we add support for the code pages listed on https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/goglobal/bb964655 that are not included yet? Or should that be left for third-party packages?
